764
00:41:42,492 --> 00:41:49,545
Rym: On your turn, you'll have a hand of cards and you either say, "I have something," or, "I want

765
00:41:49,726 --> 00:41:50,090
Rym: something.".

766
00:41:51,332 --> 00:41:53,710
Scott: So in saying that, you're giving information away.

767
00:41:53,850 --> 00:41:55,790
Scott: Obviously, if you say you have something, you have to have it.

768
00:41:55,870 --> 00:41:57,389
Scott: You can't say you have something you don't have.

769
00:41:57,911 --> 00:42:01,350
Scott: And if you say you want something, well, that's the only thing that you could get.

770
00:42:01,851 --> 00:42:07,470
Scott: So clearly, you must have something that goes with the thing you want in your hand, otherwise you wouldn't be saying that.

771
00:42:07,510 --> 00:42:08,670
Rym: So I offer a contract.

772
00:42:09,091 --> 00:42:11,250
Rym: I have two Langebaarden.

773
00:42:11,330 --> 00:42:14,629
Rym: That means I will give you two Langebaarden for whatever you offer.

774
00:42:15,030 --> 00:42:16,730
Scott: Right, so you go around the table.

775
00:42:16,811 --> 00:42:22,730
Scott: So since Rym started with an "I have," everyone else has to reply with an "I have," right?

776
00:42:23,050 --> 00:42:24,729
Scott: So Rym said he has two Langebaarden.

777
00:42:25,451 --> 00:42:26,381
Scott: I have two Schiffbau.

778
00:42:28,873 --> 00:42:30,650
