782
00:42:33,930 --> 00:42:34,948
Rym: And who cares what they are?

783
00:42:35,235 --> 00:42:35,407
Scott: Yup.

784
00:42:35,891 --> 00:42:40,549
Rym: And you go around, and then I can choose not to trade, or I can pick one of those deals and do it.

785
00:42:40,890 --> 00:42:46,490
Scott: So if he picks me, he has to give me two Langebaarden and I have to give him two Schiffbau, because that's what we said that we had.

786
00:42:46,910 --> 00:42:49,370
Rym: Oh yeah, the copy of the game we have is just in German.

787
00:42:49,510 --> 00:42:50,889
Scott: We can't negotiate, right?

788
00:42:50,930 --> 00:42:52,890
Scott: We have to do what we said was the thing.

789
00:42:53,130 --> 00:42:55,230
Rym: Yeah, it's a very structured market.

790
00:42:55,550 --> 00:42:59,428
Rym: So if I say, "I want," then Scott would say, "I

791
00:42:59,488 --> 00:42:59,830
Rym: want.".

792
00:42:59,951 --> 00:43:02,324
Scott: Yeah, you have to reply to a "want" with a "want" and a "have" with a

793
00:43:02,345 --> 00:43:02,570
Scott: "have.".

794
00:43:02,631 --> 00:43:06,570
Scott: So if he says he wants a Schiffbau, I have to, A, have to have a Schiffbau.

795
00:43:06,670 --> 00:43:09,947
Scott: I can't say I want something if I don't have the Schiffbau that he wants.

796
00:43:10,551 --> 00:43:17,990
Rym: So to step it up a little further, you can have up to two clauses and an "and" or an "or" between them.

797
00:43:18,050 --> 00:43:22,084
Rym: So I could say, "I want two Schiffbau or two

798
00:43:22,726 --> 00:43:23,409
Rym: Langebaarden.".

799
00:43:24,072 --> 00:43:29,590
Scott: So that means I can reply with a "want" as long as I have either two Schiffbau or two Langebaarden.

800
00:43:30,391 --> 00:43:32,043
Scott: And then I would say, "I want

801
00:43:32,264 --> 00:43:32,667
Scott: something.".

802
00:43:33,130 --> 00:43:39,570
Scott: So now, if we actually, Rym chooses me for the deal, it's up to me whether to give him the Schiffbaus or the Langebaarden.

803
00:43:39,630 --> 00:43:43,570
Scott: Because I said "or," I decide which of those "ors" I'm going to give.

804
00:43:43,730 --> 00:43:47,510
Rym: Yeah, so if I say, "I have X or Y," fuck you.

805
00:43:48,173 --> 00:43:49,690
Rym: You don't get to pick which one.

806
00:43:50,090 --> 00:43:56,250
Rym: So "I have or" is kind of a dick deal, but you can use that to share information.

