00:44:15,690 --> 00:44:17,348
Rym: No one did that because I don't think you can.

813
00:44:18,110 --> 00:44:22,864
Scott: Because when I give him, if you give someone something after an "or," you give it to them.

814
00:44:22,905 --> 00:44:27,749
Scott: face down so that only you and they know what you actually gave and no one else does.

815
00:44:27,950 --> 00:44:28,448
Rym: So think about this.

816
00:44:29,933 --> 00:44:33,487
Rym: When I'm saying my "haves" and "wants," I might have a part of the clause.

817
00:44:33,507 --> 00:44:36,530
Rym: that is something I actually want to do, but I'm also trying to share information.

818
00:44:36,714 --> 00:44:37,470
Rym: I'm trying to impart.

819
00:44:38,131 --> 00:44:50,149
Rym: Say it's my turn and I offer something to Scott, I might also be saying something because I want Chris to offer me something on his turn, and I'm trying to share information without saying too much information.

